cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.PL 

The paper discusses the use of reinforcement learning for adjusting hyperparameters of algorithms in the fields of hard combinatorial problem solving, machine learning, and AI in general. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to these fields, such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper introduces new benchmarks for studying algorithm control, which could also place it in sub-categories such as cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.PL (Programming Languages).
